## 🛑 Dos and Don'ts

### Website Maintenance
**✅ DO:**
- Compress images before uploading them to the codebase to maintain fast loading speeds.
- Check mobile responsiveness after adding any new text or sections.
- Keep the Contact page and "WhatsApp Button" active globally for instant buyer connection.

**❌ DON'T:**
- Don't change `id` or `class` names of forms (like the Quotation form) without updating the corresponding JavaScript logic.
- Don't use heavy, uncompressed videos natively on the site; upload them to YouTube/Vimeo and embed them.

### GitHub & Vercel Deployment
**✅ DO:**
- Commit your code with clear messages (e.g., "Updated home page banner").
- Verify the build locally using `npm run build` before pushing to GitHub to prevent live errors.
- Monitor the Vercel dashboard occasionally to ensure zero build failures.

**❌ DON'T:**
- Don't push sensitive passwords or API keys to GitHub. Always use `.env` variables in Vercel.
- Don't interrupt a Vercel deployment while it says "Building". Wait for it to finish.

### Zoho CRM & Email Automations
**✅ DO:**
- Regularly test the "Contact Us" and "Quotation" forms on the website to ensure leads flow into Zoho CRM seamlessly.
- Use the provided B2B Email Sequence as a foundation, updating pricing or product specs whenever your catalog changes.
- Ensure the WhatsApp number (`+91 7219053645`) is actively monitored to answer automated replies.

**❌ DON'T:**
- Don't change the email DNS settings in Hostinger/Vercel. It will break Zoho CRM authentication.
- Don't send bulk emails without an "Unsubscribe" link; it violates anti-spam rules.
